Revisit Thermal Equilibrium

1. Under T.E. can we have electrostatic ﬁeld (or voltage) within the semiconductor?
Yes. (we do not have “external” energy source). There can be static electrostatic ﬁeld
inside the semiconductor generated by “space” charges.

2. Under T.E. can we have an overall current? 
No. That will give rise to charge piling up. 

